<datafield ind1="0" ind2=" " tag="511">
<subfield code="a">
Speakers and participants include Dah Takin, Lucien Takin, Nestor Takin, Tangninon Takin, Noukoumiam Takin family (Ouidah); Monika Höhne (Berlin); Fred Rael, Anthony Rael, Israel Martinez, Victor Martinez (Española); Alan Bard, Steve Ballard, Rand Bennett, Charles Bunch, Lauren Ivey Chiong, Eric Christopher, Dana Dale, Lil D, BIlly Daniel, Ray Guillemette, Jr., Trent Greene, Cavon Hashemian, Jack Howard, Mark Hunt, Dwight Isenhour, Mike Maple, Marv McQueen, Joe Mendonca, Jason Michael, Jacques Millette, David Pasco, Sybil Presley, George Thomas, Michael Vegas (Memphis); Edna Mae Zonnie, Angus Hatahlie, Carol Hatahlie, Calvin Hatahlie, T.J. Redmustache (Navajo Nation); Shoba Kuma, N. Chandra Kumar, Ragi Saggere (Bangalore); Louis Padilla (Chimayo); Koh Beng Hock, Chan family (Penang); and many others.
</subfield>
</datafield>
<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
<subfield code="a">
The collection consists of the moving image and sound footage, shot between 2000 and 2003, which led to the documentary film Mana : Beyond Belief (2004). Documents created during production and post-production are also included (logs, translations, shot lists, and notes). The 114 hours of raw footage depict object veneration in Italy, Japan, Benin, France, the United States, the Navajo Nation, Malaysia, Burma, India, New Zealand, and Germany. The footage encompasses subjects such as: a rare exhibition of the Holy Shroud of Turin; the Fushimi Inari Taisha shrine in Kyoto; vodou ceremonies and The Door of No Return in Ouidah; the holy dirt of Chimayo; Navajo hogan and sweat lodge ceremonies; a modern-day dime museum in Baltimore; the one-year anniversary ceremony held at the ruins of the World Trade Center twin towers in New York City; Hindu idol-anointing in Penang; Shwedagon pagoda in Rangoon; a Burmese car-blessing shrine; an Indian IT company in Bangalore; several interviews in New Zealand about the Maori concept of mana; fine art analysis in Berlin; and more.
</subfield>
</datafield>
<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="545">
<subfield code="a">
Producer/director Peter Friedman has won many of the top awards for documentary film in the USA and Europe, and he has served on the competion juries of major European film festivals. Friedman's films include Wizard of the Strings (1985), Silverlake Life: The View From Here (1993), and Death by Design (1997).
</subfield>
</datafield>
<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="545">
<subfield code="a">
Producer/director Roger Manley's books, exhibitions, and documentation of the folklife of indigenous peoples have earned him international recognition in the fields of outsider art, anthropology, and photography. His books include Signs and Wonders: Outsider Art Inside North Carolina (1989), The Tree of Life: the Inaugural Exhibition of the American Visionary Art Museum (1996), and Self-Made Worlds: Visionary Folk Art Environments (1997).
</subfield>
</datafield>
